title: Federal Labor open to passing welfare card for Ceduna
text: The Federal Government is optimistic the Senate will soon pass legislation for a trial of it's so called 'Healthy Welfare Card', aimed at reducing alcohol-related violence in Ceduna, in the far west of South Australia. Debate on the card is due to start in the Upper House today. Labor is open to supporting the card but wants more detail before it's prepared to allow the legislation to pass. ...
